<title>UK: Barr &amp; Wallace to sell leisure division.</title>
<headline>Barr &amp; Wallace to sell leisure division.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-05-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>Barr &amp; Wallace Arnold Trust Plc said on Thursday that it is inviting offers for its lesiure division.  </p>
<p>It said in a statement it is inviting offers in light of &quot;substantial commercial interest.&quot;</p>
<p>The company also said that negotiations with Leisureplus continue.</p>
<p>It had revealed in March that it was in talks with Leisureplus, a holding company of the Shearings group, over the possible sale of its leisure division.</p>
<p>-- London Newsroom +44 171 542 4019</p>
